&lt;/ul&gt;</description></item><item><title>Magnet Push-Based Shuffle Service</title><link>https://ashishdoneriya.github.io/interview/magnet-push-based-shuffle-service.html</link><pubDate>Fri, 19 Jun 2026 01:00:00 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://ashishdoneriya.github.io/interview/magnet-push-based-shuffle-service.html</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;The paper &lt;strong&gt;“Magnet: Push-based Shuffle Service for Large-scale Data Processing”&lt;/strong&gt; is from LinkedIn.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The useful part is this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Spark shuffle becomes slow at large scale because reducers read billions of tiny shuffle blocks from disk/network. Magnet fixes that by converting tiny fragmented shuffle blocks into larger merged blocks before reducers fetch them.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id="core-problem"&gt;Core Problem&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The central problem is not:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;“Spark is slow”&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;“Network is slow”&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The real problem is:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Tiny random reads.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>System Design Resources</title><link>https://ashishdoneriya.github.io/interview/system-design-resources.html</link><pubDate>Fri, 19 Jun 2026 01:00:00 +0530</pubDate><guid>https://ashishdoneriya.github.io/interview/system-design-resources.html</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="high-level"&gt;High Level&lt;/h2&gt;
